Following allegations of gross misconduct levelled against the Deputy Governor, Hon Agboola Ajayi, the Speaker of Ondo State House of Assembly, Rt. Hon.Bamidele Oleyelogun, has asked the Chief Judge of the state, Justice Olaranwaju Akeredolu, to set up a seven-man panel to investigate him. 14 members of the Assembly that are loyal to the governor of the state, Oluwarotimi Akeredolu had on Tuesday served impeachment notice on the deputy governor. According to the Speaker, the setting up of the panel was in line with section 188 (5) of the 1999 Constitution as amended. The letter reads, “By the Resolution of the House today pursuant to Section 188 (3) and (4) of the 1999 Constitution as amended it was resolved that the allegations be investigated forthwith. “It is in line with the above that request that you set up the 7-man panel to conduct the investigation as resolved by the Honourable House and the Panel, shall soon as possible, report back to the House.” 